<section xml:id="section-vectors-matrices-linear-systems" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Vectors, Matrices and Linear Systems of Equations</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      In this section, we learn the basic notions underlying linear algebra: vectors, matrices and linear systems of equations. Many of the later concepts of linear algebra build on these elementary objects and the operations defined on them.
    </p>
  </introduction>

